	<h2>Welcome
	</h2>
	<div class="column1">
	  <p>
	    This site explains Taoist Classical Feng Shui including basic theory, practical design suggestions common ground with western science and alternatives.
	  </p>
	  <h3>Introduction
	  </h3>
	  <p>
	    Geomancy is a method of reading the Earths (sometimes planets and beyond) effect on us.
	    <b>Geo
	    </b> = earth,
	    <b> Mancy
	    </b> = divination or reading.
	    <br/>
	    <br/>
	    Many Ancient Cultures, including Aboriginal (Shamanic), African tribes, American Indian (Shamanic), Celtic, Chinese, Egyptian, Indian, Nordic (including Viking), South American (Mayan and Inca), have their own systems. Most are not really relevant today. They vary in sophistication from African tribe stick throwing divination to Renaissance metaphysics (which was a very prolific period of combining science with spiritual dimensions.  
	    <br/>
	    <br/>
	    The Chinese Taoist Art of Feng Shui is the most comprehensive and well documented type.
	    It involves a very detailed site analysis, including a Personal Horoscope, to guide on what needs changing are to achieve an environmental balance.
	    There's no magic/faith involved, it is a very precise and logical practice.
	    <br/>
	    <br/>
	    <i>A lot of modern "pseudo" feng shui borrows from other sources including "the new age" and "shamanic" ideas. This is not classical Feng Shui, it is, more like, "interior design" with a spiritual angle.
	    </i>
	  <p/>
	  <p>Classical Feng Shui is an amalgam of the Form, Compass and Flying Star Schools. 
	    <br/>
	  </p>
	</div>
	<!-- side column -->
	<div class="column2 pcenter">
